<i>These next few days,</i>

2
00:01:41,900 --> 00:01:44,540
you guys are all heading off to college.

3
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:45,960
So today,

4
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,500
our families got together

5
00:01:47,540 --> 00:01:50,440
to throw you a little send-off.

6
00:01:50,980 --> 00:01:52,800
And, well,

7
00:01:52,840 --> 00:01:54,740
since you're all 18 now,

8
00:01:54,780 --> 00:01:57,160
you're officially allowed
a little sip of alcohol.

9
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,360
- Really?
- Dad…

10
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:01,080
We're students. No drinking for us.

11
00:02:01,580 --> 00:02:03,040
Don't think I don't know who's been

12
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:04,780
dipping into that bottle of <i>Wuliangye</i>

13
00:02:04,820 --> 00:02:05,660
in the cabinet.

14
00:02:05,700 --> 00:02:06,840
Isn't it you guys' doing?

15
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:07,880
Come on, fess up.

16
00:02:07,920 --> 00:02:09,060
How did he find out?

17
00:02:09,100 --> 00:02:10,960
- They drink it?
- Did they?

18
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:13,480
<i>- These kids.</i>
- Fangyuan, come on, pour everyone a glass.

19
00:02:15,420 --> 00:02:16,260
<i>Do you want one?</i>

20
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:17,600
<i>Pour it up.</i>

21
00:02:17,640 --> 00:02:18,520
<i>Pour me one too.</i>

22
00:02:18,560 --> 00:02:20,340
Forget it.
If you don't wanna smile, don't.

23
00:02:20,380 --> 00:02:21,440
<i>Let's have a drink.</i>

24
00:02:21,480 --> 00:02:23,280
- <i>…yeah, that'll do.</i>
- Wait.

25
00:02:23,320 --> 00:02:24,340
Where's your amber necklace?

26
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:25,360
You're not wearing it.

27
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,480
<i>We are not having that in normal days.</i>

28
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:29,380
<i>- Can I have a sip?</i>
<i>- Today, let's…</i>

29
00:02:29,420 --> 00:02:32,540
It disappeared right after
Jiang Qiaoxi came back

30
00:02:32,580 --> 00:02:33,500
last time.

31
00:02:33,540 --> 00:02:35,560
<i>Here…</i>

32
00:02:35,600 --> 00:02:36,840
<i>Come on now, kids.</i>

33
00:02:36,880 --> 00:02:37,760
<i>Listen up.</i>

34
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,980
I know

35
00:02:39,020 --> 00:02:40,560
you've snuck drinks before,

36
00:02:40,600 --> 00:02:42,840
but you don't actually
know how to drink yet.

37
00:02:42,880 --> 00:02:43,720
Let me show you.

38
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:45,900
When you drink,

39
00:02:45,940 --> 00:02:47,840
hold the glass with your right hand,

40
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,960
support the base with your left.

41
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:51,780
When you toast someone,

42
00:02:51,820 --> 00:02:53,200
make sure your glass

43
00:02:53,240 --> 00:02:54,800
is a little lower than theirs.

44
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,200
You know why?

45
00:02:56,240 --> 00:02:58,220
It shows respect.

46
00:02:58,260 --> 00:02:59,720
Respect. Respect!

47
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,020
- Respect…
- No no, please.

48
00:03:01,060 --> 00:03:02,680
- I should be respecting you.
- Come on, cheers.

49
00:03:02,720 --> 00:03:04,200
- Let's all drink together.
- Cheers.

50
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,180
- Happy days.
- Cheers.

51
00:03:05,220 --> 00:03:06,320
Cheers.

52
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:10,880
You drank it all?

53
00:03:10,920 --> 00:03:11,940
Yu Qiao.

54
00:03:12,900 --> 00:03:14,500
Yun, Yingtao, listen up.

55
00:03:14,540 --> 00:03:16,840
When you're out there,
you can't drink at will.

56
00:03:16,880 --> 00:03:18,600
Especially you girls.

57
00:03:18,640 --> 00:03:20,860
No matter what happens,
don't let yourselves get drunk.

58
00:03:20,900 --> 00:03:21,880
Got it?

59
00:03:21,920 --> 00:03:23,480
- When have you ever seen
- Got it.

60
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,360
my daughter drink?

61
00:03:24,400 --> 00:03:25,900
Uncle Cai, we hear you.

62
00:03:25,940 --> 00:03:26,920
If anyone's getting drunk,

63
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,600
it's whoever tries to keep up
with Qin Yeyun.

64
00:03:31,640 --> 00:03:34,020
- He's kidding. Just jokes.
- Oh, jokes.

65
00:03:34,060 --> 00:03:35,980
Once you're out there on your own,

66
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,860
you'll have to rely on yourselves.

67
00:03:38,900 --> 00:03:40,080
You've got to learn

68
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,160
to keep your eyes open and ears sharp.

69
00:03:42,200 --> 00:03:43,420
When you run into trouble,

70
00:03:43,460 --> 00:03:45,340
use your head. Think it through.

71
00:03:46,140 --> 00:03:48,280
If it's tough, try to push through.

72
00:03:49,420 --> 00:03:50,860
And if you can't,

73
00:03:52,140 --> 00:03:53,300
come home

74
00:03:53,340 --> 00:03:54,520
and talk to us.

75
00:04:03,260 --> 00:04:04,800
That's, um, that's all I've got.

76
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:07,740
You guys say something.

77
00:04:08,280 --> 00:04:09,680
Say a few words.

78
00:04:10,380 --> 00:04:12,040
Alright, I'll say a little.

79
00:04:12,080 --> 00:04:14,580
All I hope is you

80
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:18,680
eat well, sleep well, and study well.

81
00:04:18,720 --> 00:04:20,060
Try to be one of those

82
00:04:20,100 --> 00:04:21,440
Model Students, okay?

83
00:04:22,280 --> 00:04:23,120
And don't worry

84
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:24,820
about things back home.

85
00:04:27,240 --> 00:04:28,500
We've got it covered.

86
00:04:28,540 --> 00:04:29,860
That's me. I'm done.

87
00:04:33,140 --> 00:04:33,980
Here.

88
00:04:37,260 --> 00:04:39,820
Every person is born with a purpose.

89
00:04:39,860 --> 00:04:42,220
Raise your sails and ride the waves.

90
00:04:42,880 --> 00:04:44,620
I wish you all

91
00:04:44,660 --> 00:04:45,560
a bright future.

92
00:04:50,380 --> 00:04:51,220
Thank you.

93
00:04:53,280 --> 00:04:54,340
My turn.

94
00:04:54,380 --> 00:04:55,880
You're making this way too serious.

95
00:04:55,920 --> 00:04:56,980
Go on, go on.

96
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,080
Your dad's stepping up.

97
00:05:06,220 --> 00:05:08,720
I don't usually talk much,

98
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:10,260
but today I have to say something.

99
00:05:11,880 --> 00:05:13,100
From now on,

100
00:05:13,140 --> 00:05:15,560
you've got to take care of yourselves.
Live your own lives.

101
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,860
Of course, I hope everything you run into

102
00:05:17,900 --> 00:05:19,340
will be good things,

103
00:05:19,380 --> 00:05:21,580
nothing bad at all.

104
00:05:21,620 --> 00:05:22,980
But think about it.

105
00:05:23,020 --> 00:05:24,780
How could anyone

106
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:25,960
go through life

107
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:27,900
with only good things happening?

108
00:05:28,760 --> 00:05:30,700
There's no way you can get through it

109
00:05:30,740 --> 00:05:31,860
without hurtful things,

110
00:05:31,900 --> 00:05:33,200
without something

111
00:05:33,240 --> 00:05:34,700
that breaks your heart.

112
00:05:34,740 --> 00:05:35,580
Right?

113
00:05:36,080 --> 00:05:37,440
So remember this.

114
00:05:37,480 --> 00:05:39,760
Whatever pain you're feeling right now,

115
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,220
it'll pass.

116
00:05:41,260 --> 00:05:42,980
Even the bad things

117
00:05:43,020 --> 00:05:45,700
can turn into something good, eventually.

118
00:05:47,260 --> 00:05:48,860
And one last thing. Someone once said,

119
00:05:49,360 --> 00:05:51,880
when you wade through
the river of your life,

120
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,700
every bit of joy and pain you feel

121
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:58,480
will become part of the scenery.

122
00:05:58,520 --> 00:06:01,180
And you are the best part of it.

123
00:06:01,220 --> 00:06:02,100
Well said!

124
00:06:02,640 --> 00:06:03,760
Beautifully said.

125
00:06:03,800 --> 00:06:04,820
So good.

126
00:06:08,420 --> 00:06:09,320
Alright. Now is time

127
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:11,300
for a word from the moms.

128
00:06:11,340 --> 00:06:13,220
- Baoxuan. Say something.
- Come on.

129
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:15,600
What would I even say?

130
00:06:15,640 --> 00:06:16,760
Feels kinda cheesy.

131
00:06:17,400 --> 00:06:18,360
I'll pass.

132
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:20,400
Be safe out there.

133
00:06:20,440 --> 00:06:22,080
- Thank you.
- Hey, come on.

134
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:23,480
Why are you crying?

135
00:06:23,520 --> 00:06:25,180
It's a happy day, remember?

136
00:06:25,220 --> 00:06:26,060
Yeah, happy.

137
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:30,420
Are we being too loud?
Maybe we're disturbing the neighbors.

138
00:06:31,040 --> 00:06:32,680
- Maybe.
- I'll get the door. I'll get it.

139
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,640
Yingtao, your surprise is here.

140
00:06:34,680 --> 00:06:35,720
Wait for it.

141
00:06:36,460 --> 00:06:37,520
Surprise?

142
00:06:38,180 --> 00:06:39,140
What surprise?

143
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:40,800
Jiang Qiaoxi?

144
00:06:42,740 --> 00:06:43,600
Hello.

145
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,540
You are…

146
00:06:48,580 --> 00:06:50,920
Come in, come in. Don't block the doorway.

147
00:06:52,600 --> 00:06:53,860
- Is he…?
- Yingtao.

148
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:56,520
You don't remember Chen Minghao?

149
00:06:57,680 --> 00:07:00,200
Look how grown up you are now, Yingtao!

150
00:07:00,240 --> 00:07:02,040
Chen Minghao?

151
00:07:02,080 --> 00:07:03,320
Hello, Aunties and Uncles.

152
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:05,560
- Hello!
- Sit.

153
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,520
- Have a seat.
- Come.

154
00:07:06,560 --> 00:07:07,480
- Come.
- Sit.

155
00:07:07,520 --> 00:07:09,580
You brought so many gifts too?

156
00:07:09,620 --> 00:07:10,800
Minghao,

157
00:07:10,840 --> 00:07:12,340
how are your parents?

158
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:14,620
They're doing well. Just super busy.

159
00:07:14,660 --> 00:07:16,400
Otherwise, they would've come with me.

160
00:07:17,100 --> 00:07:18,340
They're always saying

161
00:07:18,380 --> 00:07:21,500
Uncle Cai and Auntie Kang
took such good care of my grandparents.

162
00:07:21,540 --> 00:07:22,820
Since I finally came back,

163
00:07:22,860 --> 00:07:24,440
they insisted I come visit.

164
00:07:24,480 --> 00:07:26,900
We're all neighbors from back in the day.
No need to be so formal.

165
00:07:26,940 --> 00:07:28,360
Your grandma was always

166
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,660
looking out for us.

167
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,520
She'd share anything good she had with us.

168
00:07:32,140 --> 00:07:34,360
Where are you studying abroad, Minghao?

169
00:07:34,860 --> 00:07:36,240
Australia, Uncle Yu.

170
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:38,700
Australia?

171
00:07:39,200 --> 00:07:41,020
That must cost a fortune

172
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:42,340
to study there.

173
00:07:42,960 --> 00:07:45,980
Well, it really depends
on the universities and the location.

174
00:07:46,020 --> 00:07:47,960
The costs can vary a lot.

175
00:07:48,500 --> 00:07:49,840
Yun could do her undergrad here

176
00:07:49,880 --> 00:07:51,620
and apply for grad school in Australia.

177
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,540
Dad, stop daydreaming.

178
00:07:55,580 --> 00:07:57,540
School's school.
Don't care about going abroad.

179
00:07:59,940 --> 00:08:01,160
Minghao,

180
00:08:01,960 --> 00:08:03,560
have you been living alone

181
00:08:03,600 --> 00:08:04,980
all these years?

182
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:06,120
Yeah, just me.

183
00:08:06,160 --> 00:08:08,400
It it hard being abroad on your own?

184
00:08:09,080 --> 00:08:10,780
Was it easy to find food?

185
00:08:10,820 --> 00:08:12,140
Did you make any friends?

186
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:16,960
Is it tough speaking
another language all the time?

187
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,580
I manage okay.

188
00:08:18,620 --> 00:08:21,120
But those who work while studying
really have it rough.

189
00:08:21,160 --> 00:08:24,280
Classes during the day,
waiting tables at night.

190
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,860
My parents don't allow me to work at all.

191
00:08:27,360 --> 00:08:29,520
They say if I'm there to study,
then I should just focus.

192
00:08:29,560 --> 00:08:31,760
They even rented me a place off-campus.

193
00:08:31,800 --> 00:08:33,640
On weekends I can
throw parties with friends.

194
00:08:33,679 --> 00:08:34,720
Can't complain.

195
00:08:35,299 --> 00:08:36,659
Your parents are so nice.

196
00:08:37,679 --> 00:08:38,640
Yingtao,

197
00:08:38,679 --> 00:08:41,340
I heard you got into
Northern Normal University.

198
00:08:41,980 --> 00:08:43,320
You used to be that sweet little girl

199
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:45,080
with the red bead necklace

200
00:08:45,120 --> 00:08:46,580
always chasing after me.

201
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:48,280
Now you're headed to a top university.

202
00:08:48,780 --> 00:08:49,840
That's amazing.

203
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:51,940
Thanks.

204
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:55,160
But it wasn't a red bead.

205
00:08:55,200 --> 00:08:56,300
It was amber.

206
00:08:56,340 --> 00:08:59,140
Oh! My bad. Sorry about that.

207
00:08:59,180 --> 00:09:00,740
<i>Minghao, eat more.</i>

208
00:09:03,380 --> 00:09:04,780
<i>Come on, everyone, dig in.</i>

209
00:09:04,820 --> 00:09:05,660
<i>Here, help yourself.</i>

210
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,120
Alright. You guys can head back.

211
00:09:08,160 --> 00:09:09,500
- Bye-bye.
- See you, Minghao.

212
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:11,260
Take care!

213
00:09:12,160 --> 00:09:13,100
- Bye!
- Bye!

214
00:09:13,140 --> 00:09:14,200
Bye-bye!

215
00:09:17,480 --> 00:09:19,960
Why'd you suddenly bring Minghao here?

216
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:23,320
That was your big surprise
for Lin Yingtao?

217
00:09:23,360 --> 00:09:25,440
Du Shang, come on. You explain

218
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:27,740
why we set this whole thing up.

219
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:29,880
Yingtao.

220
00:09:30,660 --> 00:09:31,640
Have you really forgotten?

221
00:09:31,680 --> 00:09:33,840
Back when we all saw Minghao off,

222
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,160
you cried

223
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,560
like the world was ending.

224
00:09:37,060 --> 00:09:38,100
You cried so hard,

225
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:40,060
it felt like the whole town
could hear you.

226
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,820
But look at today.
You barely even recognized him.

227
00:09:42,860 --> 00:09:44,300
So yeah,

228
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:46,480
get ready to soak up
the whole college experience.

229
00:09:47,580 --> 00:09:48,660
Because one day,

230
00:09:49,160 --> 00:09:50,620
when you think about that person,

231
00:09:50,660 --> 00:09:52,200
you might feel just like this.

232
00:09:55,420 --> 00:09:56,440
Really?

233
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,580
Of course.

234
00:10:01,960 --> 00:10:03,880
But that person is Jiang Qiaoxi.

235
00:10:05,980 --> 00:10:07,520
- What?
- You two

236
00:10:07,560 --> 00:10:09,220
really think you're geniuses, huh?

237
00:10:10,780 --> 00:10:11,960
<i>Wait…</i>

238
00:10:12,000 --> 00:10:14,280
<i>- We didn't do anything wrong.</i>
<i>- What do you mean?</i>

239
00:10:14,320 --> 00:10:15,660
<i>Can't you see she's upset?</i>

240
00:10:15,700 --> 00:10:17,240
Why'd you rush off like that?

241
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:22,180
I was just thinking,

242
00:10:23,360 --> 00:10:24,900
if Jiang Qiaoxi hadn't been around,

243
00:10:25,720 --> 00:10:26,560
I probably

244
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:28,340
wouldn't have worked so hard
in middle school.

245
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,800
Wouldn't have gotten
into Experimental High,

246
00:10:31,360 --> 00:10:32,980
Wouldn't have made it to Northern Normal.

247
00:10:34,460 --> 00:10:35,760
That came out of nowhere.

248
00:10:35,800 --> 00:10:37,360
Bit of a sharp turn there.

249
00:10:41,020 --> 00:10:42,360
I had to say it while I remembered.

250
00:10:45,460 --> 00:10:46,500
Where is he now anyway?

251
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:50,320
No idea.

252
00:10:52,680 --> 00:10:53,660
It's alright.

253
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:55,200
I'll help you find out.

254
00:10:55,240 --> 00:10:56,200
I mean, he still

255
00:10:57,160 --> 00:10:58,120
has to go to college.

256
00:10:59,720 --> 00:11:01,140
We'll hear from him eventually.

257
00:11:04,500 --> 00:11:05,480
I think so too.

258
00:11:08,640 --> 00:11:10,820
By the way, Lin Yingtao,

259
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:14,520
Northern Aviation and Northern Normal
are barely three kilometers apart.

260
00:11:14,560 --> 00:11:16,060
We're even registering just a day apart.

261
00:11:16,100 --> 00:11:17,940
So why don't you want to go together?

262
00:11:19,520 --> 00:11:21,880
I just wanted to see what it feels like

263
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:25,420
leaving home completely on my own

264
00:11:25,460 --> 00:11:26,980
and stepping into something new.

265
00:11:49,420 --> 00:11:50,440
Yingtao,

266
00:11:51,180 --> 00:11:53,060
I think Jiang Qiaoxi's kind of

267
00:11:53,560 --> 00:11:54,700
a jerk.

268
00:11:56,420 --> 00:11:57,640
Look at him.

269
00:11:57,680 --> 00:11:59,300
Before he left for Hong Kong,

270
00:11:59,340 --> 00:12:02,060
he gave you lipstick and red heels.

271
00:12:02,620 --> 00:12:05,120
Once you turn 18,
you're not just a girl anymore.

272
00:12:05,160 --> 00:12:07,200
You're starting to become a woman.

273
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,460
And lipstick and heels?
That's a woman's starter kit.

274
00:12:09,500 --> 00:12:11,800
He gave those to you
