00:28:15,480 --> 00:28:17,840
I'm alright.

545
00:28:20,240 --> 00:28:22,240
Why, do you want me to be?

546
00:28:23,760 --> 00:28:24,980
So you're not scared?

547
00:28:27,040 --> 00:28:28,720
You just don't look like the brave type.

548
00:28:31,600 --> 00:28:32,980
Actually,

549
00:28:33,020 --> 00:28:34,480
I know a ghost story too.

550
00:28:34,520 --> 00:28:35,520
Wanna hear it?

551
00:28:41,400 --> 00:28:43,420
Ever heard the story

552
00:28:44,600 --> 00:28:46,460
of two best friends, back to back?

553
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:50,500
There were these two girls,
Qiqi and Yueyue.

554
00:28:51,440 --> 00:28:54,160
They were roommates,

555
00:28:54,200 --> 00:28:55,400
close as sisters.

556
00:28:56,640 --> 00:28:58,480
They shared a bunk bed,

557
00:28:58,520 --> 00:29:02,080
and every night they'd stay up talking.

558
00:29:02,620 --> 00:29:03,620
One night,

559
00:29:04,120 --> 00:29:05,800
they started chatting about something

560
00:29:05,840 --> 00:29:09,360
that happened at school on the 15th day
of the seventh lunar month.

561
00:29:10,420 --> 00:29:12,860
Legend says that one year,
on that exact day,

562
00:29:12,900 --> 00:29:14,980
a pair of best friends

563
00:29:15,020 --> 00:29:18,360
got into a fight over something small
and ended up killing each other.

564
00:29:18,400 --> 00:29:21,440
Ever since then,
people say you can still hear them arguing

565
00:29:22,140 --> 00:29:23,720
in the dorm halls on the 15th day

566
00:29:23,760 --> 00:29:25,760
of the seventh lunar month every year.

567
00:29:26,640 --> 00:29:28,680
So Qiqi and Yueyue made a plan.

568
00:29:28,720 --> 00:29:31,160
This year, they were
going to that building

569
00:29:31,200 --> 00:29:33,400
to see for themselves.

570
00:29:34,120 --> 00:29:35,260
But

571
00:29:35,300 --> 00:29:37,620
just a few days before the 15th,

572
00:29:38,540 --> 00:29:41,240
Yueyue vanished.

573
00:29:42,620 --> 00:29:46,220
Qiqi waited… and waited.

574
00:29:46,260 --> 00:29:48,580
She stayed up till midnight,

575
00:29:49,220 --> 00:29:50,840
but Yueyue never came back.

576
00:29:51,740 --> 00:29:53,220
Suddenly, the phone rang.

577
00:29:53,260 --> 00:29:55,200
There was no voice on the other end.

578
00:29:55,960 --> 00:29:57,160
Qiqi said,

579
00:29:58,260 --> 00:29:59,420
"Hello, Yueyue?

580
00:29:59,920 --> 00:30:01,720
Say something. Yueyue?"

581
00:30:03,620 --> 00:30:06,300
Finally, a soft voice came through,

582
00:30:09,440 --> 00:30:12,260
"I'm… so cold."

583
00:30:14,960 --> 00:30:17,000
Qiqi thought it was a prank

584
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:18,120
and hung up.

585
00:30:18,620 --> 00:30:21,480
But the next night, right at midnight,

586
00:30:22,280 --> 00:30:24,160
Yueyue called again,

587
00:30:25,980 --> 00:30:27,920
"I'm so cold."

588
00:30:30,680 --> 00:30:32,060
Third night. Same call.

589
00:30:32,980 --> 00:30:34,080
Fourth night. Still cold.

590
00:30:34,580 --> 00:30:36,440
It went on and on until the seventh day,

591
00:30:37,860 --> 00:30:39,520
the 15th.

592
00:30:40,640 --> 00:30:42,320
Yueyue called one more time.

593
00:30:43,240 --> 00:30:45,080
Qiqi couldn't take it anymore.

594
00:30:45,120 --> 00:30:47,120
"Come back." She said.

595
00:30:47,160 --> 00:30:48,820
"Stop messing with me!"

596
00:30:49,580 --> 00:30:51,260
But then Yueyue whispered,

597
00:30:51,900 --> 00:30:53,920
"I never left.

598
00:30:54,420 --> 00:30:57,180
We're best friends, remember?
Back to back."

599
00:30:57,220 --> 00:30:59,240
Qiqi panicked.

600
00:30:59,280 --> 00:31:01,180
She ducked under the covers.

601
00:31:02,200 --> 00:31:03,880
But she couldn't sleep.

602
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:05,460
She kept tossing and turning.

603
00:31:06,360 --> 00:31:07,960
Finally, she rolled over

604
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:11,060
and saw Yueyue.

605
00:31:11,100 --> 00:31:12,940
But it wasn't her.

606
00:31:12,980 --> 00:31:16,980
It was her skin.

607
00:31:17,660 --> 00:31:20,140
And just then,
a voice whispered in her ear,

608
00:31:20,820 --> 00:31:22,140
"See?

609
00:31:22,180 --> 00:31:24,120
I told you I was here.

610
00:31:25,040 --> 00:31:28,240
Best friends… back to back.

611
00:31:28,280 --> 00:31:29,400
My dear best friend…

612
00:31:31,800 --> 00:31:33,800
Look at me."

613
00:31:44,260 --> 00:31:47,900
Junior Lin, that was
actually a pretty good story.

614
00:31:47,940 --> 00:31:49,140
Better than mine.

615
00:31:49,640 --> 00:31:52,260
I'm stealing that for my boyfriend.

616
00:31:52,760 --> 00:31:53,640
I'm going to sleep.

617
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:54,620
We should all sleep.

618
00:31:55,120 --> 00:31:58,100
I've heard too many of these.
Kinda boring now.

619
00:31:58,140 --> 00:32:00,580
Yeah, we… um, we've got class tomorrow.

620
00:32:11,660 --> 00:32:14,240
<i>Today was my first night in the new dorm.</i>

621
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:15,140
SEND TO JIANG QIAOXI

622
00:32:15,180 --> 00:32:17,820
<i>But the senior girls</i>
<i>all tried to scare me off.</i>

623
00:32:18,580 --> 00:32:20,700
<i>They told ghost stories</i>
<i>to get me to leave.</i>

624
00:32:21,520 --> 00:32:22,740
<i>I wasn't scared.</i>

625
00:32:23,700 --> 00:32:24,900
<i>I scared them back.</i>

626
00:32:26,440 --> 00:32:27,620
<i>Jiang Qiaoxi,</i>

627
00:32:28,700 --> 00:32:29,960
<i>how have you been?</i>

628
00:32:31,100 --> 00:32:32,360
<i>Are the people around you</i>

629
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:34,020
<i>treating you well?</i>

630
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:03,760
What are you doing?

631
00:33:05,480 --> 00:33:07,480
I want her to come
to the bathroom with me.

632
00:33:09,340 --> 00:33:12,560
Junior Lin, come pee with me?

633
00:33:13,380 --> 00:33:14,240
What's happening?

634
00:33:14,280 --> 00:33:15,560
Bathroom, please?

635
00:33:23,700 --> 00:33:24,960
It's fine.

636
00:33:30,900 --> 00:33:32,160
You're fine, senior.

637
00:33:41,920 --> 00:33:43,000
How far is it?

638
00:33:44,060 --> 00:33:46,720
Hurry up, come on. One, two, three.

639
00:33:49,360 --> 00:33:51,220
Nope! That's not it!

640
00:33:51,260 --> 00:33:52,240
That made me jump.

641
00:33:52,800 --> 00:33:54,060
Though someone was there.

642
00:33:55,960 --> 00:33:56,940
Come on.

643
00:34:06,660 --> 00:34:08,260
Junior Lin, hey.

644
00:34:08,300 --> 00:34:09,400
Why don't we share

645
00:34:09,900 --> 00:34:10,800
the same bed tonight?

646
00:34:18,179 --> 00:34:20,120
I mean, I guess that's fine.

647
00:34:22,020 --> 00:34:22,900
There's room.

648
00:34:33,920 --> 00:34:37,480
You were totally freaked out, weren't you?

649
00:34:39,020 --> 00:34:40,219
I was alright.

650
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:42,080
But seriously,

651
00:34:42,659 --> 00:34:45,940
you don't get scared
telling ghost stories?

652
00:34:49,139 --> 00:34:51,219
Actually, I have a magic spell.

653
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:53,739
A spell?

654
00:34:58,920 --> 00:35:00,380
"Ghost, ghost,

655
00:35:00,880 --> 00:35:02,640
if you're here,

656
00:35:02,680 --> 00:35:04,000
can you turn on the light for me?"

657
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:08,120
What kind of spell is that?

658
00:35:08,160 --> 00:35:09,180
Is it a summoning spell?

659
00:35:09,920 --> 00:35:12,240
Look,

660
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:15,200
if the ghost turns on the light,

661
00:35:15,240 --> 00:35:17,340
that means it's a friendly ghost.

662
00:35:17,380 --> 00:35:18,600
It won't hurt you.

663
00:35:19,100 --> 00:35:20,880
If it doesn't,

664
00:35:20,920 --> 00:35:22,920
then it's a weak ghost with no powers,

665
00:35:22,960 --> 00:35:24,040
and still won't hurt you.

666
00:35:25,880 --> 00:35:28,000
Where did you even hear that?

667
00:35:28,540 --> 00:35:29,840
My dad told me.

668
00:35:31,120 --> 00:35:32,500
It's just something

669
00:35:33,340 --> 00:35:34,560
to comfort you mentally.

670
00:35:35,400 --> 00:35:37,660
And your fear of ghost is pure mentally.

671
00:35:38,220 --> 00:35:40,300
There's no such thing anyway.

672
00:35:44,220 --> 00:35:45,640
That kind of makes sense.

673
00:35:46,140 --> 00:35:47,380
Let me try.

674
00:35:47,920 --> 00:35:48,820
"Ghost,

675
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,320
if you're really here,

676
00:35:51,360 --> 00:35:53,140
turn the light on for me."

677
00:35:58,240 --> 00:35:59,580
What are you two doing

678
00:35:59,620 --> 00:36:01,240
sharing one bed?

679
00:36:01,900 --> 00:36:03,660
- I am scared…
- In the middle of the night

680
00:36:03,700 --> 00:36:05,700
and you're chatting with ghosts?

681
00:36:05,740 --> 00:36:09,900
Who was that talking to me?

682
00:36:11,480 --> 00:36:12,520
Get up.

683
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:14,760
Bunch of scaredy-cats trying to

684
00:36:14,800 --> 00:36:16,800
freak someone out,
then scaring ourselves instead.

685
00:36:16,840 --> 00:36:18,000
Unbelievable.

686
00:36:22,740 --> 00:36:24,100
Seniors,

687
00:36:25,420 --> 00:36:27,340
I guess I owe you an apology

688
00:36:27,380 --> 00:36:29,020
for scaring you back.

689
00:36:29,780 --> 00:36:31,360
But you started it,

690
00:36:31,400 --> 00:36:33,760
telling ghost stories to freak me out.

691
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,000
See?

692
00:36:36,040 --> 00:36:38,600
Look at this kid, holding a grudge.

693
00:36:39,460 --> 00:36:41,760
So we scared you,
and you just had to scare us back?

694
00:36:41,800 --> 00:36:44,400
I just wanted to show you
I'm not easy to push around.

695
00:36:45,160 --> 00:36:46,940
You can't get rid of me that easily.

696
00:36:46,980 --> 00:36:47,880
Get rid of you?

697
00:36:47,920 --> 00:36:50,000
Why would we want to do that?

698
00:36:50,040 --> 00:36:51,020
Yeah.

699
00:36:51,060 --> 00:36:52,760
You're cute. You're fun.

700
00:36:53,300 --> 00:36:55,480
We adore you. Why would we kick you out?

701
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:56,980
How could you…

702
00:36:58,760 --> 00:36:59,920
I heard everything.

703
00:37:03,200 --> 00:37:04,840
I was standing outside the door.

704
00:37:04,880 --> 00:37:06,980
You said you didn't like
roommates like me.

705
00:37:07,020 --> 00:37:08,920
Said you didn't want to live with me.

706
00:37:08,960 --> 00:37:11,000
Said you'd find a way to make me leave.

707
00:37:11,540 --> 00:37:14,220
I was so scared,
I didn't even dare come back.

708
00:37:14,260 --> 00:37:16,360
I sat downstairs by myself
until the doors locked.

709
00:37:16,400 --> 00:37:19,060
I only came up
because I thought you were all asleep.

710
00:37:19,100 --> 00:37:19,940
The moment I laid down,

711
00:37:19,980 --> 00:37:21,780
you started telling ghost stories
to scare me.

712
00:37:23,360 --> 00:37:24,960
What's so funny?

713
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:26,140
See?

714
00:37:26,180 --> 00:37:29,880
That's why taking things
out of context is dangerous.

715
00:37:30,380 --> 00:37:33,240
Is freshman bootcamp ending today?

716
00:37:34,300 --> 00:37:36,280
Is that Lin girl coming back?

717
00:37:37,700 --> 00:37:39,140
I'm telling you,

718
00:37:39,180 --> 00:37:42,080
we should never have been
that loud the other day.

719
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:44,140
We probably scared her half to death.

720
00:37:45,840 --> 00:37:48,100
None of us were sober, though.

721
00:37:48,140 --> 00:37:49,540
Stupid booze ruined everything.

722
00:37:51,280 --> 00:37:53,640
She seemed so quiet and polite.

723
00:37:53,680 --> 00:37:55,820
What if she's really afraid of us now?

724
00:37:57,560 --> 00:37:58,780
Is she thinking of changing rooms?

725
00:37:59,320 --> 00:38:00,860
Wouldn't be that surprising if she did.

726
00:38:02,140 --> 00:38:02,980
If I were her,

727
00:38:03,020 --> 00:38:04,740
I wouldn't want roommates like us.

728
00:38:06,020 --> 00:38:08,380
Then do something about it.

729
00:38:09,940 --> 00:38:11,420
Wanna try something that hits her

730
00:38:11,460 --> 00:38:12,300
right in the feels?

731
00:38:12,340 --> 00:38:13,700
How?

732
00:38:13,740 --> 00:38:15,200
"Misattribution of arousal,

733
00:38:15,240 --> 00:38:18,060
also known as the
Capilano Suspension Bridge Effect,

734
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:19,320
is a psychological phenomenon."

735
00:38:19,860 --> 00:38:20,820
Basically,

736
00:38:20,860 --> 00:38:21,960
when someone goes through

737
00:38:22,000 --> 00:38:23,480
intense emotions,

738
00:38:23,520 --> 00:38:25,680
like fear or excitement

739
00:38:25,720 --> 00:38:28,380
their heart starts racing,
blood pressure rises,

740
00:38:28,420 --> 00:38:30,300
they breathe faster.

741
00:38:30,340 --> 00:38:32,700
All those physical reactions

742
00:38:32,740 --> 00:38:34,620
can get misread as romantic attraction

743
00:38:34,660 --> 00:38:38,340
to whoever's with them in that moment.

744
00:38:38,380 --> 00:38:39,720
Oh, that's easy.

745
00:38:41,020 --> 00:38:42,640
We just tell her a scary ghost story.

746
00:38:43,160 --> 00:38:44,920
Once her heart's pounding

747
00:38:44,960 --> 00:38:46,220
and she's all worked up,

748
00:38:46,720 --> 00:38:47,840
Meng Lijun,

749
00:38:47,880 --> 00:38:49,420
you swoop in like a caring senior

750
00:38:50,060 --> 00:38:51,820
and let her sleep in your bed.

751
00:38:51,860 --> 00:38:53,560
And then,

752
00:38:53,600 --> 00:38:55,340
after one night together,

753
00:38:55,380 --> 00:38:56,780
boom, bond formed.

754
00:38:58,060 --> 00:38:59,920
You guys are unbelievable.

755
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:00,900
You…

756
00:39:00,940 --> 00:39:04,400
You guys are seniors. Seniors!
And you're still this childish?

757
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:05,440
So what?

758
00:39:08,560 --> 00:39:11,420
You're actually kinda sweet though.

759
00:39:11,460 --> 00:39:13,060
Thought we were trying to kick you out,

760
00:39:13,100 --> 00:39:14,920
and you still walked me to the bathroom.

761
00:39:14,960 --> 00:39:16,600
Even shared your bed with me.

762
00:39:19,620 --> 00:39:20,580
Senior,

763
00:39:21,500 --> 00:39:22,600
so,

764
00:39:22,640 --> 00:39:23,520
do you like me?

765
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:26,940
Do you like me?

766
00:39:28,680 --> 00:39:30,320
I feel like you kinda do.

767
00:39:31,980 --> 00:39:34,020
Guess that bridge effect thing

768
00:39:34,060 --> 00:39:35,440
might be onto something after all.

769
00:39:35,480 --> 00:39:36,460
Right?

770
00:39:37,360 --> 00:39:38,560
Right, right.

771
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:40,240
Makes sense. I'm telling you.

772
00:39:40,280 --> 00:39:42,420
Next time I'm dating someone,

773
00:39:42,460 --> 00:39:43,560
I'm using this trick.

774
00:39:44,440 --> 00:39:46,360
- Totally foolproof.
- Guaranteed to work.

775
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:47,480
Seriously.

776
00:40:04,760 --> 00:40:05,800
Yingtao, look.

777
00:40:06,400 --> 00:40:07,600
Another nightly performance.

778
00:40:08,100 --> 00:40:09,340
It's louder

779
00:40:09,380 --> 00:40:11,020
than the Spring Festival Gala in here.

780
00:40:14,300 --> 00:40:15,280
Come on.

781
00:40:16,200 --> 00:40:17,360
- What?
- Come on.

782
00:40:17,860 --> 00:40:19,900
Lijun, can you call Sisi for me?

783
00:40:20,660 --> 00:40:22,400
Boys aren't allowed in the girls' dorm.

784
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:30,420
Lijun, um…

785
00:40:30,460 --> 00:40:32,000
He's not here for me.

786
00:40:33,480 --> 00:40:34,780
Then for who?

787
00:40:34,820 --> 00:40:37,300
<i>That's Sisi's boyfriend, Shi Zhan.</i>

788
00:40:37,800 --> 00:40:39,800
Oh, they had a fight?

789
00:40:39,840 --> 00:40:41,300
He came to apologize?

790
00:40:42,200 --> 00:40:43,360
It's not that simple.

791
00:40:43,400 --> 00:40:44,980
They're both seniors.

792
00:40:45,660 --> 00:40:49,180
Shi Zhan wants to move back to Shandong
and get a public school teaching job.

793
00:40:49,220 --> 00:40:50,260
But Sisi

794
00:40:50,300 --> 00:40:53,060
is going back to Suzhou
to try for a civil service job.

795
00:40:53,100 --> 00:40:56,160
Shi Zhan wants her
to go with him, get married.

796
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:58,220
Sisi wants to break up.

797
00:41:02,640 --> 00:41:03,540
WOMEN'S DORM MEN KEEP OUT

798
00:41:03,580 --> 00:41:06,260
She never mentioned this.

799
00:41:06,300 --> 00:41:09,040
She doesn't want to.
And we're not gonna push her.

800
00:41:10,300 --> 00:41:12,620
Remember the day you arrived,
when we were all hungover?

801
00:41:13,120 --> 00:41:14,500
We were talking about it the night.

802
00:41:27,480 --> 00:41:28,520
Is he still downstairs?

803
00:41:32,900 --> 00:41:33,940
Yeah.

804
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,660
Sisi.

805
00:42:06,020 --> 00:42:07,280
Sisi!

806
00:42:08,340 --> 00:42:10,140
What are you doing?

807
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,060
<i>A relationship takes two people.</i>

808
00:42:14,560 --> 00:42:17,180
<i>You can't just decide everything</i>
<i>on your own.</i>

809
00:42:18,240 --> 00:42:19,260
<i>Sisi!</i>

810
00:42:20,280 --> 00:42:22,260
Is this it?

811
00:42:23,540 --> 00:42:24,800
Yeah.

812
00:42:34,640 --> 00:42:35,760
It's fine. I…

813
00:42:36,800 --> 00:42:37,860
I told him…

814
00:42:40,400 --> 00:42:43,160
Told him not to stand there
getting all emotional by himself.

815
00:42:43,700 --> 00:42:46,120
Honestly, I knew from the start

816
00:42:47,460 --> 00:42:48,980
we'd break up after graduation.

817
00:42:50,340 --> 00:42:52,460
It just happened
a year earlier than expected.

